Boris Arkadyevich Kopeikin (Russian:   ) (born March 27, 1946 in Chelyabinsk) is a retired Soviet football player and a current Russian coach. Kopeikin made his debut for USSR on October 28, 1970 in a friendly against Bulgaria. He played in the UEFA Euro 1972 qualifiers, but was not selected for the final tournament squad. 
